text.section:
The following moneys may not be considered general funds of the State and shall be deposited into the Insurance Regulation Fund established under Subtitle 5 of this title:
all revenue received through the imposition and collection of the assessment fee under Subtitle 5 of this title;
all revenue received through the imposition and collection of the fees set forth in § 2-112 of this subtitle;
all revenue received through the imposition and collection of the fraud prevention fee under Title 6, Subtitle 2 of this article;
all revenue received through the collection of examination expenses under § 2-208 of this title;
except as provided under subsection (a) of this section, all other fees received through the imposition and collection of fees set forth in this article; and
income from investments that the State Treasurer makes for the Insurance Regulation Fund.
